oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Grand Army of the Republic veteran medal
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: This Grand Army of the Republic veteran medal belonged to Pvt. William Wilkerson Masters of Co. M, 8th Tenn. Cav. Regt., USA. He walked with his brother Alexander to Knoxville to join the Union army and served from May 31, 1863, until September 11, 1865. Masters (1837-1914) lived in what was then Washington County, but is now Unicoi County, Tennessee.
